<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2721] nodetool statusthrift exception while node starts up</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2721</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We noticed when calling nodetool statusthrift, while a node is starting up, it throws an exception. I think the proper behavior should be just return false, instead of throwing an exception if RPC server hasn&apos;t started yet. That way this stack trace won&apos;t have to be thrown in nodetool:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.IllegalStateException: No configured RPC daemon&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12508683">CASSANDRA-2721</key>
            <summary>nodetool statusthrift exception while node starts up</summary>
